Herat is the third largest city of Afghanistan .The city is linked with Kandahar and Mazar-e-Sharif via highway 1.
Thousands of internally displaced people are flocking to Herat province in Afghanistan, fleeing severe droughts and violence in other parts of the country.
Around 40,000 people have been dislocated to Herat this year alone.
Life have become very difficult in this War-torn country.
